\displaystyle \lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{1}{n} \sin \dfrac{t}{n} + \sin \dfrac {2t}{n} + ... + \sin \dfrac{(n-1)t}{n}  = \dfrac{1 - \cos \space t}{t}
\displaystyle \lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{1}{n} \displaystyle \sum ^n _{k=1} \sin \dfrac{kt}{n} = \displaystyle \int_0 ^t \sin x \space dx = 1 - \cos \space t 
\displaystyle \lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{1}{n} \displaystyle \sum ^{n-1} _{k=1} \sin \dfrac{kt}{n} =  \dfrac {1 - \cos t}{t} 
 \lim_{n\rightarrow \infty} \frac{1}{n} \sum_{k=1}^n \sin{\frac{k t}{n}} = \int_0^1 \sin(xt) dx = \left[\frac{-\cos{xt}}{t} \right]^1_0 
